# Pre-Introduction
When we do different task on our computer like opening an email or connecting to the Internet or ..., we are actually doing it by favor of our operating system.
the Operating system sits on top of our hardware and controlls it and does what we tell it to do.

! - More than 96% of world's server computers and almost all supercomputers use Linux.

What is it with linux? why is it so popular and useful? we'll find out soon!.

In this path we'll learn a lot about how to install and configure a system, 
manage users and permissions, understand services & network and troubleshoot them precisely.

Doesn't matter if we are a Devops rookie or a simple sysadmin or even scientist and developer, mastery over linux concepts means more control and less error in our work.

### The goals of this course:
- Deep and structured comprehension of Linux.
- Gain engineering & analysis vision over the system.
- Manage the system: install, Configure, work with FileSystems.
- Mastery over Terminal, fast-paced work and automation.
- Increasing basic security and control, and set ownerships and permissions.
- Increase stability and troubleshooting ability: like checking processes, logs and services for issue.
- Create a firm and strong foundation for further roles (like devops or sysadmin) and development (lpic2).
